properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 2:46AM MST until February 1 at 12:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Watch for the Cody Foothills This Evening through
Saturday Morning...

.Favorable weather conditions will develop over the Cody
Foothills for strong westerly winds to occur after sunset this
evening into Saturday morning.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts around 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills. The strongest winds will occur just
south of Cody, as well as between Clark and junction of
Highway 120 and the Chief Joseph Highway.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening through Saturday morning. The
strongest winds are expected between 4 AM and 9 AM Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Enhanced blow over risk
for light and high profile vehicles especially along highway
120.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING
